edu.caltech.nanodb.sqlparse

Class NanoSqlParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • antlr.Parser
      • antlr.LLkParser
        • edu.caltech.nanodb.sqlparse.NanoSqlParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NanoSqlParserTokenTypes

    public class NanoSqlParser
extends antlr.LLkParser
implements NanoSqlParserTokenTypes
    A parser for processing SQL commands into the various command-classes derived from Command. The information in these commands is then used for data-definition, data-manipulation, and general utility operations, within the database.

      • expression

        public final Expression expression()
                            throws antlr.RecognitionException,
                                   antlr.TokenStreamException
        The expression rule matches pretty much any possible logical and/or mathematical expression that one might need. Note that it will parse a lot of expressions that don't make any sense because of type-matching requirements, but that is fine - this parse rule is about determining the appropriate structure of the expression, and that is about applying operator precedence and following the form of the expressions. Semantic analysis catches the nonsensical statements.
        Throws:
        antlr.RecognitionException
        antlr.TokenStreamException
